<a name="323"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>FoH reason for the nerf....AND..</b> <font size=2>(Score: 0)<br>by Anonymous on Thursday, February 22 @ 13:51:18 EST</font></td></tr><tr><td>heh, you'll have to excuse me for posting under Xarn's comment, I'm a newbie to this board.  My friends told me this was the best place to see information on what will happen with this change to the healing system.<br>
<br>
Basicly what it boils down to is this:  They completely and utterly changed the <b>Healing</b> system this game provides after 2 years plus of released service.  Weapon proc, warrior defensive broken, evade change...all can be worked around, they are minor changes, and probly for the better in my opinion.  However, changing the way one person heals another has ruined the game...RUINED.<br>
<br>
Let me share something with everyone.  I have a friend who works for Verant in the testing department.  He knows very much about this game and how it works, etc etc.  Yes, FoH's ability to conquer mobs so fast because they are very intelegent and dedicated to the game was one of the primary reasons of this nerf.  They were not supposed to be this far in the game.  The REAL reason this nerf happened was because they awakened the sleeper.  <br>
<br>
Here is a little info on The Sleeper.  Verant has a special scrip written for when the Sleeper is awakened.  As said by my friend, "he is supposed to spawn in other areas of Norrath and permanently change part of the game as we know it."  Well guess what, they are NOT even close to being done with the coding for him.  He was not told about what they plan on doing, because they don't want it to get out, wuch as this info.<br>
<br>
I'm sure FoH knows most of this, and they also know that Sleeper's Tomb is far from finished itself.  Most items there are not made and ready for the game yet.  Those cloth caps you got off one of the dragon protectors are mearly place holders in their loot table until the items they have planned are in the game and finished. <br>
<br>
Same goes for Temple of Veeshan, loot is not finished.  Reason is these mobs were not expected to be killed for some time yet.  With these new changes to the healing system, they made sure that they will never be killed...never.<br>
<br>
Let me tell you how much this was play tested in house at Verant headquarters.  Z-E-R-O.  My friend is an in house play tester, and he had NO idea this was happening.  None.  You see, getting the sleeper to awake was not supposed to happen yet, and it was a emergency to get people away from the mobs asap.  They have succeeded.<br>
<br>
<br>
Verant just drove the nail all the way into their death of Everquest.  I can guarentee this game is dead in 2-3 months max, if not sooner.  Verant just has no clue; no idea how fed up people are of this game.  Only reason people still play is because of friends in the game, or they have a need to play an on-line game, and this is the ONLY one out there....at this moment.  Only a couple months until SB, AO, and UO2...gonna be great to cancel my account.  Nothing better then having to eat verant's shit for over a year and a half, then to be able to cut off the money I send them every month.  <br>
<br>
Qalar Rubican<br>
Cats in Hats<br>
